1 year after one of my worst days: STILL ALIVE

Everyone makes a big deal of anniversaries & I never really got it but I guess itâ€™s because we like to think of all the good things around and share them because these good things mean we are growing and changing and our skin is stretching and that is all good. I have known horrible things that have made my skin stretch and made me grow and change, so I think we should make space for those & celebrate having lived through those too, despite how morbid they might have been. Our darkest moments, like our brightest are detrimental to our development as little bags of skins and bones that feel joy and pain and the rain on our skin & Iâ€™m done feeling shame for having lived those!! If itâ€™s okay to burst out laughing then itâ€™s also okay to burst out crying because we FEEL it all. So here's a horrible & morbid anniversary: on this day a year ago I was hospitalized because life got too much (as it often does). Now it has been a year and I am older, and I am scared and, I am guilty and, I am happy, and I am confused, and I am still healing and parts of me never left that place or that hallway and some of them never will. Despite that & most importantly: I still am. In that fight, in that defeat, in that relapse, and in that return from the warm gloomy abyss I am not alone. We keep living and hope the gaps between the bad times get bigger and the length of the bad times gets shorter and with that hope we make it through the minutes.Â Â So, I want to thank the world for its kindness, appreciate its bitterness, and I want to ask for some more kindness to help me through the week and i want to offer the same in return. Itâ€™s a hard time of year and I have felt how it can feel like your entire life is on a bed where nothing ever happens and the world goes on around you outside bulletproof windows and all u can do it is watch life pass you by from a dim hallway. I have (and am) surviving from the kindness of strangers. So, whoever you are, if you need someone, I can be your person. Let me know if I can help you through this time because it is a hard time and it is hard to go it alone. You donâ€™t have to go it alone.
